reviewText:
Only made it halfway through.

The Bad:
Acting

Directing
Camera Work
Acting (deserved a second mention)
Pretty much everything

The Good:
Story Idea
The grain of the wood on the door to the men's restroom at his work.(wanted more than one thing, and it is really nice)
This movie was a riot. I laughed the whole time. Very entertaining, in a sick and twisted sort of way.

Lame. One simple word for a movie that wants to be like a Troma film but sucks hard core at it and that is saying a lot here. All you need for a Good Troma like film is good gore, humor and a couple of wtf moments all that this movie lacks. Only two acts in the film had gore worth of a Troma film and only one I found funny which ramped this film up from the one start I was set on giving it and he shot a dog, I hate dog killing, and last if you were looking for over the top poop jokes there not here either regardless of what the pic on the vid looks like.

Well, firstly you need to go into this knowing it is bad, low budget cinema (obviously). If you are okay with that and like butt humor, you'll probably get some shreds of entertainment in this. I found myself laughing out loud on more than one occasion at the absurdity. It's the kind of script a few drunk high school kids might come up with.
Save a hour of your life shoot yourself first, before suffering threw watching this!  Its that bad!  I guess his mom must have giving it a "5".

This movie will only be entertaining if you find potty humor funny. Farts, skidmaks in Underwear and losing control of ones bowels. I fortunately do find some of this funny.

There are quite a bit of bloody killings but they're rather silly and of course it's all meant to be tongue in cheek . If you're with friends that are like minded give it a watch a have a hoot and a holler! It's mindless fun that requires no concentration.
I think I just developed IBS trying to watch this mess.

Very funny.  The best line was about going to the bar where there are plenty of skunk p*ssies just waiting to be picked up for a stink bang.  James Costa is really securing his position as a major independent actor here.  Another incredible performance.  This movie is very raunchy, gory, and funny!
